$lang['The hexadecimal system is a base 16 number notation, while the decimal system is a base 10 number notation. In other words, the hexadecimal system uses 16 symbols to represent numbers, while the decimal system uses 10 symbols. This expansion also allows for a higher information density-hexadecimal digits can represent twice as many values as decimal digits.'] = 'Endlelo ra hexadecimal i notation ya nomboro ya base 16, kasi sisiteme ya decimal i notation ya nomboro ya base 10. Hi marito man’wana, endlelo ra hexadecimal ri tirhisa swikombiso swa 16 ku yimela tinomboro, kasi endlelo ra decimal ri tirhisa swikombiso swa 10. Ku ndlandlamuxiwa loku ku tlhela ku pfumelela density ya mahungu ya le henhla-tidijithali ta hexadecimal ti nga yimela mimpimo yo tala kambirhi ku tlula tidijithali ta desimali.';
$lang['Hexadecimal numbers are made up of 16 digits instead of the 10 in a decimal number. The order of these numbers starts over after F (or 15 in decimal), while it doesn’t in the decimals. Check out the table below to see how they compare!'] = 'Tinhlayo ta hexadecimal ti vumbiwa hi tidijithali ta 16 ematshan’wini ya 10 eka nomboro ya desimali. Ku landzelelana ka tinomboro leti ku sungula nakambe endzhaku ka F (kumbe 15 hi desimali), kasi a ku sunguli eka tidesimali. Languta tafula leri nga laha hansi ku vona leswaku va pimanisa njhani!';
$lang['How do you convert a Hexadecimal to a Decimal?'] = 'Xana u yi hundzula njhani Hexadecimal yi va Decimal?';
$lang['When converting hexadecimal to decimal, the first step is to divide the hex number by 16. This will give you the base number. The second step is to divide each digit of the hex number by 16 and write down the results. Finally, add up all of the numbers that were just calculated.'] = 'Loko u hundzuluxa hexadecimal ku ya eka decimal, goza ro sungula i ku avanyisa nomboro ya hex hi 16. Leswi swi ta ku nyika nomboro ya xisekelo. Goza ra vumbirhi i ku avanyisa digiti yin’wana ni yin’wana ya nomboro ya hex hi 16 ivi u tsala vuyelo bya kona. Eku heteleleni, hlanganisa tinomboro hinkwato leti a ti ha ku hlayeriwa.';
$lang['For example, if someone wants to convert 9F7A to decimal, they would first divide 9F7A by 16 which equals 6051. Then they would divide each digit of 6051 by 16 which equals 381. Lastly, they would add up 381 + 381 + 381 which equals 1144. Therefore, 9F7A in decimal is equal to 1144'] = 'Xikombiso, loko munhu a lava ku hundzuluxa 9F7A yi va desimali, a a ta rhanga hi ku avanyisa 9F7A hi 16 leyi ringanaka na 6051. Kutani a a ta avanyisa digiti yin’wana na yin’wana ya 6051 hi 16 leyi ringanaka na 381. Xo hetelela, a a ta hlanganisa 381 + 381 + 381 leyi ringanaka 1144. Hikwalaho, 9F7A hi desimali yi ringana na 1144';
$lang['How do you convert a Decimal to a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Xana u yi hundzula njhani Decimal yi va Hexadecimal?';
$lang['Converting decimal to hexadecimal is a simple process, and can be done with a calculator or online converter. In order to convert the number, divide it by 16 and take the remainder. This remainder will then correspond to a hexadecimal digit. For example, if you have the decimal number 234, divide it by 16 and take the remainder: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Therefore, in hexadecimal notation, this number would be written as “E2”.'] = 'Ku hundzuluxa decimal kuya eka hexadecimal i endlelo ro olova, naswona swinga endliwa hi calculator kumbe online converter. Leswaku u hundzula nomboro, yi avanyisa hi 16 ivi u teka leyi saleke. Kutani leswi saleke swi ta fambelana na digiti ya hexadecimal. Xikombiso, loko u ri na nomboro ya desimali ya 234, yi avanyisa hi 16 ivi u teka leyi saleke: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Hikwalaho, eka notation ya hexadecimal, nomboro leyi a yi ta tsariwa tanihi “E2”.';
$lang['There are many tools available online that can help with converting between decimal and hexadecimal numbers. Additionally, most calculators have a built-in function that will allow you to do this conversion very easily. With just a few clicks of the mouse or taps on the keyboard, you’ll be able to change any decimal value into its corresponding hexadecimal equivalent!'] = 'Kuna switirhisiwa swotala leswi kumekaka eka inthanete leswinga pfunaka eka ku hundzuluxa exikarhi ka tinomboro ta decimal na hexadecimal. Ku engetela kwalaho, swikalo swo tala swi ni ntirho lowu akiweke endzeni lowu nga ta ku pfumelela ku endla ku hundzuka loku hi ku olova swinene. Hi ku tsindziyela swi nga ri swingani ntsena swa mbeva kumbe ku ba eka khibhodi, u ta kota ku cinca ntikelo wihi na wihi wa desimali wu va lowu ringanaka na wona wa hexadecimal!';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Hexadecimal over a Decimal?'] = 'Hi yihi mimpfuno ya ku tirhisa Hexadecimal ku tlula Decimal?';
$lang['The hexadecimal, or base-16, system was designed to emulate some of the same properties as the decimal system. In other words, it was created to make things easier for us humans. The number 423 has 16 digits instead of 10 digits available in a decimal system. This is because hexadecimal uses a base of 16 symbols instead of 10. After F, the order begins again with 0 and so on and so forth until we get to 15 which is notated as F.'] = 'Endlelo ra hexadecimal, kumbe base-16, ri endleriwe ku tekelela swin’wana swa swihlawulekisi leswi fanaka ni swa fambiselo ra decimal. Hi marito man’wana, yi vumberiwe ku olovela swilo eka hina vanhu. Nomboro ya 423 yi na 16 wa tidijithali ematshan’wini ya 10 wa tidijithali leti kumekaka eka sisiteme ya desimali. Leswi swi vangiwa hikuva hexadecimal yi tirhisa xisekelo xa swikombiso swa 16 ematshan’wini ya 10. Endzhaku ka F, ku landzelelana ku sungula nakambe hi 0 na swin’wana na swin’wana ku kondza hi fika eka 15 leyi tsariweke tanihi F.';
$lang['Hexadecimal encoding reduces the number of digits by a factor of eight when compared to the decimal system. Additionally, hexadecimal numbers have an information density that is twice as high as decimal numbers do. So, why should you bother learning this funky little numbering scheme? Because it can make your life easier! When working with digital systems or data transmission, using hex will save you time and energy when decoding cryptic messages or data streams.'] = 'Ku khoda ka hexadecimal ku hunguta nhlayo ya tidijithali hi factor ya tsevu loko ku pimanisiwa na sisiteme ya decimal. Ku engetela kwalaho, tinomboro ta heksadesimali ti ni nhlayo ya rungula leyi tlakukeke kambirhi ku tlula tinomboro ta desimali. Kutani, ha yini u fanele u tikarhata hi ku dyondza xikimi lexi xa tinomboro lexitsongo xa funky? Hikuva swi nga olovisa vutomi bya wena! Loko u tirha na tisisiteme ta xidijitali kumbe ku hundziseriwa ka data, ku tirhisa hex swi ta ku hlayisela nkarhi na matimba loko u decoding marungula ya xihundla kumbe swirhendzevutani swa data.';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Decimal over a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Hi yihi mimpfuno ya ku tirhisa Decimal ku tlula Hexadecimal?';
$lang['When it comes to binary coding, Hexadecimal is more efficient because it reduces 8 digits to 2. Additionally, Hex provides a greater degree of information density and higher accuracy in numbers than binary does. This is due to the fact that Hex uses 16 symbols instead of just two like binary. Because of this increased efficiency, Hexadecimal is often used when binary coding in computing and digital electronics as well as for computer science applications.'] = 'Loko swi ta eka ku khoda ka binary, Hexadecimal yi tirha kahle swinene hikuva yi hunguta tidijithali ta 8 ku ya eka 2. Ku engetela kwalaho, Hex yi nyika mpimo lowukulu wa ku hlangana ka mahungu na ku pakanisa ka le henhla eka tinomboro ku tlula binary. Leswi swi vangiwa hileswi Hex yi tirhisaka swikombiso swa 16 ematshan’wini ya swimbirhi ntsena ku fana na binary. Hikwalaho ka ku engeteleka loku ka vukorhokeri, Hexadecimal yi tala ku tirhisiwa loko ku endliwa tikhodi ta binary eka khomphyuta na elektroniki ya xidijitali xikan’we na switirhisiwa swa sayense ya tikhompyuta.';
$lang['In addition, Hexadecimal takes up less space than decimal. With only two digits instead of 8 binary digits, Hex numbers represent large numbers much more concisely. This can be very helpful when working with computer systems, as there is less chance for mistakes when typing in hex codes compared to decimal codes which have so many decimal points all over the place!'] = 'Ku engetela kwalaho, Hexadecimal yi teka ndhawu yitsongo ku tlula decimal. Hi tidijithali timbirhi ntsena ematshan’wini ya tidijithali ta 8 ta binary, tinomboro ta Hex ti yimela tinomboro letikulu hi ndlela yo koma swinene. Leswi swi nga pfuna swinene loko u tirha na tisisiteme ta khompyuta, tanihileswi ku nga na nkarhi wutsongo wa swihoxo loko u thayipa tikhodi ta hex loko ku pimanisiwa na tikhodi ta desimali leti nga na tinhla to tala ta desimali hinkwako!';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Hi yihi nxaxamelo wa mimpimo leyi nga yimeriwaka hi Hexadecimal?';
$lang['A hexadecimal number is a number that uses 16 digits instead of the 10 digits we use in the decimal system. This number system is called base-16, and it helps us to emulate the properties of our familiar decimal system. In hexadecimal, each digit represents a power of 16. The numbers 0 through 9 represent the powers of 1 through 10, while A through F represent the powers of 11 through 15.'] = 'Nomboro ya hexadecimal i nomboro leyi tirhisaka 16 wa tidijithali ematshan’wini ya 10 wa tidijithali leti hi ti tirhisaka eka sisiteme ya desimali. Endlelo leri ra tinomboro ri vuriwa base-16, naswona ri hi pfuna ku tekelela swihlawulekisi swa fambiselo ra hina ra desimali leri hi ri toloveleke. Hi hexadecimal, digiti yin’wana na yin’wana yi yimela matimba ya 16. Tinhlayo ta 0 ku ya eka 9 ti yimela matimba ya 1 ku ya eka 10, kasi A ku ya eka F yi yimela matimba ya 11 ku ya eka 15.';
$lang['Just like in decimal, after 16 symbols have been used in Hexadecimal, the order of numbers starts over again at zero. So, hexadecimal 10 is equal to decimal 16, and hexadecimal 11 is equal to decimal 17. And so on!'] = 'Ku fana na le ka desimali, endzhaku ka loko ku tirhisiwile swikombiso swa 16 eka Hexadecimal, ku landzelelana ka tinomboro ku sungula nakambe eka ziro. Kutani, hexadecimal 10 yi ringana na decimal 16, naswona hexadecimal 11 yi ringana na decimal 17. Na swin’wana!';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Decimal?'] = 'Hi yihi nxaxamelo wa mimpimo leyi nga yimeriwaka hi Desimali?';
$lang['The Decimal system starts with 10 and goes up to 15. This means that the range of values that can be represented by a decimal number is from 0-9, followed by A-F (10-15).'] = 'Endlelo ra Decimal ri sungula hi 10 ri ya ehenhla ku ya eka 15. Leswi swi vula leswaku nxaxamelo wa mimpimo leyi nga yimeriwaka hi nomboro ya desimali yi suka eka 0-9, yi landzeriwa hi AF (10-15).';
$lang['How do you decode Hexadecimal?'] = 'Xana u yi decode njhani Hexadecimal?';
$lang['When it comes to decoding Hexadecimal, there are a few things you need to know. First, just like the decimal system, the hexadecimal system has 10 symbols (0-9) that represent numbers. However, in hexadecimal, these digits have values that are twice as large as their counterparts in the decimal system. So, while the number “10” is represented by the symbol “A” in hexadecimal, it would be equal to “10” in the decimal system.'] = 'Loko swi ta eka ku decoda Hexadecimal, ku na swilo swi nga ri swingani leswi u faneleke ku swi tiva. Xo sungula, ku fana ni fambiselo ra desimali, endlelo ra hexadecimal ri ni swikombiso swa 10 (0-9) leswi yimelaka tinomboro. Kambe eka hexadecimal, tidijithali leti ti na mimpimo leyi phindhiweke kambirhi ku tlula ya tona eka sisiteme ya desimali. Kutani, hambileswi nomboro ya “10” yi yimeriwaka hi mfungho wa “A” hi hexadecimal, a yi ta ringana na “10” eka fambiselo ra decimal.';
$lang['Similarly, after reaching 9 in Hexadecimal (represented by “F”), we start counting again at 10 (“10”). This pattern continues until we reach 15 (“1F”), at which point we reset back to 0 and begin counting again at 16 (“20”). This might sound confusing at first, but with a little practice, it will become second nature!'] = 'Hilaha ku fanaka, endzhaku ko fika eka 9 hi Hexadecimal (leyi yimeriweke hi “F”), hi sungula ku hlayela nakambe eka 10 (“10”). Xivumbeko lexi xi ya emahlweni ku kondza hi fika eka 15 (“1F”), laha hi tlhelelaka endzhaku eka 0 ivi hi sungula ku hlayela nakambe eka 16 (“20”). Leswi swi nga ha twala swi pfilunganya eku sunguleni, kambe loko u titolovetanyana, swi ta va ntumbuluko wa vumbirhi!';
