$lang['Hexadecimal is a way of representing binary data in human-readable form. It was developed in the 19th century to allow computers to store large amounts of information.'] = 'Hexadecimal i ndlela yo yimela datha ya binary hi xivumbeko lexi hlayekaka hi vanhu. Yi endliwe hi lembe-xidzana ra vu-19 leswaku tikhompyuta ti kota ku hlayisa rungula ro tala.';
$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'U nga tirhisa hexadecimal ku hundzuluxa exikarhi ka mimpimo ya decimal na binary. Xikombiso, ku hundzuluxa 10011011001010 yi va hexadecimal swi ta endla leswaku ku va na 0x4F. Leswi swi vula leswaku ntikelo wa 4F wu yimela nomboro ya binary 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Eka tinhlayo na sayense ya tikhompyuta, hexadecimal (na yona base 16, kumbe hex) i sisiteme ya tinomboro ya xiyimo leyi nga na radix, kumbe base, ya 16. Yi tirhisa swikombiso swa khume-nhungu swo hambana, hakanyingi swikombiso swa 0–9 ku yimela mimpimo ya zero ku ya eka nhungu, . na A, B, C, D, E, F (kumbe hi ndlela yin’wana a–f) ku yimela mimpimo ya khume ku ya eka khume ntlhanu. Xikombiso, nomboro ya heksadesimali 2AF3 yi ringana, hi desimali, na (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , kumbe 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Dijiti yin’wana na yin’wana ya hexadecimal yi yimela mune wa tidijithali ta binary (bits) (leti tlhelaka ti vuriwa &quot;nibble&quot;), naswona ku tirhisiwa ko sungula ka notation ya hexadecimal i tanihi ku yimela loku nga na xinghana ka vanhu ka mimpimo ya binary coded eka khomphyuta na elektroniki ya xidijitali. Xikombiso, mimpimo ya byte yi nga suka eka 0 ku ya eka 255 (decimal) kambe yi nga ha yimeriwa hi ndlela yo olova tanihi tidijithali timbirhi ta hexadecimal eka nxaxamelo wa 00 ku ya eka FF. Hexadecimal yi tlhela yi tirhisiwa hi ntolovelo ku yimela tiadirese ta memori ya khompyuta.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex i xifunengeto xa Hexadecimal, lexi sekeriweke eka xivumbeko xa base -16 naswona xi tirhisiwa ku olovisa ndlela leyi swiletelo eka tikhompyuta swi yimeriwaka ha yona. Endlelo leri ra tinomboro ta swikombiso swa 16 ri endliwe tanihi ndlela yo sivela nomboro ya 8-bit binary, xisweswo data yi nga khodiwa eka tikhompyuta handle ko endla matshalatshala. Yi nga kandziyisiwa no thayipiwa hi ku tirhisa tidijithali timbirhi to hambana ta hex laha digiti yin’wana na yin’wana ya hex yi kombisaka nibble kumbe kumbexana xivumbeko xa 4-bits.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Endlelo leri ra tinomboro ri tirhisa swikombiso swa 16 leswi yimeriweke eka mpimo wo suka eka 0-9 kumbe AF. 0–9 yi yimela tinomboro ku fika eka nhungu kasi AF yi yimeriwile hi tinhlayo ta 10–15. Loko ku pimanisiwa na tinxaka tin’wana tinharhu ta maendlelo ya tinomboro, endlelo ra tinomboro ta hexadecimal ri tekiwa tanihi leri tirhaka swinene.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'Khodi ya wena ya hexadecimal a yi tirhi';
